The '''Electronic Municipal Market Access''' ('''EMMA''') system, operated by the [[Municipal Securities Rulemaking Board]] (MSRB), serves as the official source for [[municipal securities]] disclosures and related [[market data]] in the United States.  EMMA provides free on-line access to centralized new issue municipal securities disclosure documents (known as official statements),<ref name=recentcd>{{cite web|url=http://emma.msrb.org/MarketActivity/RecentOS.aspx|title=About the Information Available on EMMA|publisher=Emma.msrb.org|accessdate=8 December 2014}}</ref> on-going continuing disclosures for all municipal securities,<ref name=recentcd></ref> escrow deposit agreements for advance refundings (i.e., refinancings) of outstanding bonds,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://emma.msrb.org/MarketActivity/RecentAR.aspx |accessdate=December 13, 2008 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081212000843/http://emma.msrb.org/marketactivity/recentar.aspx |title=EMMA Electronic Municipal Market Access - Refunding Information |archivedate=December 12, 2008 }} </ref> real-time municipal bond trade price information,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://emma.msrb.org/MarketActivity/RecentTrades.aspx |accessdate=December 13, 2008 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081212000915/http://emma.msrb.org/marketactivity/recenttrades.aspx |title=EMMA Electronic Municipal Market Access - Recent Trades |archivedate=December 12, 2008 }}</ref> interest rates and auction results for municipal auction rate securities<ref>{{cite web|url=http://emma.msrb.org/MarketActivity/RecentARS.aspx |accessdate=October 5, 2008 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090131132647/http://emma.msrb.org/MarketActivity/RecentARS.aspx |title=EMMA Electronic Municipal Market Access - ARS data |archivedate=January 31, 2009 }} </ref> (the first free source for this kind of information on the [[auction rate securities]] market{{citation needed|date=December 2014}}) and interest rate reset information for variable rate demand obligations,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://emma.msrb.org/MarketActivity/RecentVRDO.aspx |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090729053017/http://emma.msrb.org/MarketActivity/RecentVRDO.aspx |title=EMMA Electronic Municipal Market Access - About the information available |date=July 29, 2009 |archive-date=December 12, 2008 }}</ref> together with daily statistics on trading activity<ref>{{cite web|url=http://emma.msrb.org/MarketActivity/ViewStatistics.aspx |accessdate=December 13, 2008 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081228003309/http://emma.msrb.org/MarketActivity/ViewStatistics.aspx |title=EMMA Electronic Municipal Market Access - Market Statistics |archivedate=December 28, 2008 }}</ref> and investor education materials.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://emma.msrb.org/EducationCenter/EducationCenter.aspx |accessdate=December 13, 2008 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081211041240/http://emma.msrb.org/EducationCenter/EducationCenter.aspx |title=EMMA Electronic Municipal Market Access - Overview |archivedate=December 11, 2008 }} </ref>

EMMA's disclosure collection operates in coordination with the MSRB's investor protection rules mandating that securities firms and banks selling municipal securities to customers provide them with complete disclosure of all important information about the investment.<ref name="MSRB Notice 2009-42">[http://www.msrb.org/msrb1/archive/2009/2009-42.asp MSRB Notice 2009-42] {{dead link|date=December 2014}}</ref> EMMA also is the central information utility through which municipal securities disclosures mandated by the [[Securities and Exchange Commission]] (SEC) through its Rule 15c2-12 are made freely available to the general public.<ref name="SEC Press Release on Improved Transparency in the Municipal Securities Market, December 8, 2008">{{cite web|url=https://www.sec.gov/news/press/2008/2008-286.htm|title=SEC, MSRB: New Measures to Provide More Transparency Than Ever Before for Municipal Bond Investors|work=Sec.gov|accessdate=8 December 2014}}</ref>  The EMMA continuing disclosure service provides access to audited financial statements, default notices, taxability notices, notices of rating changes, and approximately 30 additional categories of financial and other updates relating to municipal securities.<ref name=recentcd/>  The MSRB and SEC continue to work toward expanding the types and timeliness of disclosures available through EMMA.<ref name="SEC Votes to Propose Rules Enhancing Municipal Securities Disclosure, July 15, 2009">{{cite web|url=https://www.sec.gov/news/press/2009/2009-161.htm|title=Press Release: SEC Votes to Propose Rules Enhancing Municipal Securities Disclosure; 2009-161; July 15, 2009|date=15 July 2009|work=sec.gov|accessdate=8 December 2014}}</ref><ref name="MSRB Seeks to Provide Investors With Additional Disclosure Information, July 15, 2009">[http://www.msrb.org/msrb1/press/Release/MSRBSeeksToProvideInvestorsWithAdditionalDisclosureInformation.asp MSRB Seeks to Provide Investors With Additional Disclosure Information, July 15, 2009] {{dead link|date=December 2014}}</ref>

Public access to the integrated collection of primary market and secondary market disclosure provided through EMMA parallels the centralized disclosure currently available for securities offerings by public companies through the SEC's [[EDGAR]] system, although EMMA provides additional items of information beyond the base disclosures provided by EDGAR, such as trade prices, interest rates, market statistics and educational materials.  The collection of disclosure documents available through EMMA for municipal securities is not identical to what is available through EDGAR for registered offerings of corporate or other securities since municipal securities and their state & local governmental issuers are afforded broad exemptions from most provisions of the federal securities laws (such as the [[Securities Act of 1933]], the [[Securities Exchange Act of 1934]] and the [[Investment Company Act of 1940]]) otherwise applicable to private-sector issuers of corporate and other types of securities.

